[[File:Wu Siu Hong At 2009 East Asian Game Torch Reply.JPG|thumb|right|200px|[[Wu Siu Hong|Wu Siu-hong]] running with the torch]] The '''[[2009 East Asian Games]] torch relay''' was the torch relay portion prior to the opening of the [[East Asian Games]]. It took place on 29 August 2009 on the 100th day countdown to the games.<ref name="l1">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/index.php Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100126195939/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/index.php |date=2010-01-26 }}." ''Background.'' Retrieved on 2010-05-23.</ref> About 500 local schools held torch relay activities from September 2009 to November 2009 prior to the start of the games in December.<ref name="l2">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/b5/pressrelease_001.php Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100608223156/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/b5/pressrelease_001.php |date=2010-06-08 }}." ''火炬接力傳遞慶祝香港2009東亞運動會100日倒數.'' Retrieved on 2010-05-23.</ref> The torch pipe was designed by HK designer Kan Tai-keung (靳埭強).<ref name="l2" /> The relay held the theme "Light the way to the EAG".<ref name="ltorch1">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/index.php Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100126195939/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/index.php |date=2010-01-26 }}." ''The Hong Kong 2009 East Asian Games 100-day Countdown cum Torch Relay.'' Retrieved on 2010-01-24.</ref>
==Torch== The torch is a curvy cylinder with a square top and round bottom. It resembles the [[horn (anatomy)|horn]] of an [[ox]] as 2009 is the [[Ox (zodiac)|year of the Ox]].<ref name="torchr">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/torch_relay.php Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100126150009/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/torch_relay.php |date=2010-01-26 }}." ''Celebration of the 60th Anniversary of the People's Republic of China – The Hong Kong 2009 East Asian Games 100-day Countdown cum Torch Relay.'' Retrieved on 2010-01-25.</ref> They create the patterns of "Lucky Clouds" to put forward the concept of [[yin and yang]]. This also convey the message that Hong Kong is a place where the Chinese and Western cultures meet.<ref name="torchr" />
==Torch relay route== The relay point begins at [[Kowloon Park]] that travels to [[Austin Road]] and [[Nathan Road]]. Then it turns to [[Salisbury Road, Hong Kong|Salisbury Road]] and [[Tsim Sha Tsui East]] before reaching the [[Avenue of Stars, Hong Kong|Avenue of Stars]] and [[Kowloon Public Pier]]. The bearers then cross [[Victoria Harbour]] by water and reach Expo drive east on the other side of the harbour. It continues to Harbour Road before going to Expo drive and finish at the [[Golden Bauhinia Square]] with the last torch bearer.<ref name="ltb">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/torchbearer.php Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100611201256/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/en/torchbearer.php |date=2010-06-11 }}." ''Torchbearers.'' Retrieved on 2010-05-23.</ref>
==Torchbearers== There were a total of 65 torchbearers. The route was divided by 3 sections.<ref name="ltb" /><ref name="lrp">Lcsd.gov.hk. "[http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/doc/tb_allotment_e.pdf Lcsd.gov.hk] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110612025034/http://www.lcsd.gov.hk/2009eagTorchRelay/doc/tb_allotment_e.pdf |date=2011-06-12 }}." ''Routing plan.'' Retrieved on 2010-05-23.</ref>
