{{Infobox stadium | location = View of the East Stand at Balmoor | opened = 1997 | image = Peterhead, Balmoor Stadium.jpg | image_size = 250px |coordinates = {{coord|57|30|42.10|N|1|47|45.05|W|type:landmark|display=inline}} | surface = [[Lawn|Grass]] | owner = [[Peterhead F.C.]] | capacity = {{SPFL-stadiums|peterhead}}<ref name="capacity"/> (1,000 seated) | record_attendance = 4,855 (vs [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]], 20 January 2013) | dimensions = 105 × 70 yards | tenants = [[Peterhead F.C.]] }}
'''Balmoor''' (also known as '''Balmoor Stadium''') is an [[association football]] [[stadium|ground]] in the [[Scotland|Scottish]] town of [[Peterhead]], [[Aberdeenshire]]. It is home to [[Scottish League One|Scottish League]] Two side [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]]. The stadium has a capacity of {{SPFL-stadiums|peterhead}}<ref name="capacity">{{cite web |url=http://spfl.co.uk/clubs/peterhead/ |title=Peterhead Football Club|publisher=Scottish Professional Football League |accessdate=11 November 2013}}</ref> spectators of which 1,000 can be seated.<ref name = "BBC">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18735027|title=Rangers: Life in Scottish Division Three beckons|accessdate=20 January 2013}}</ref>
The ground was opened in 1997, after [[Peterhead F.C.|Peterhead]]'s old ground Recreation Park was sold off to [[supermarket]] company [[Safeway (UK)|Safeway]].<ref name = "guide">{{cite news|url=http://www.footballgroundguide.com/scotland/peterhead.html|title=Peterhead|work=Scottish Ground Guide|publisher=Duncan Adams|accessdate=8 January 2012}}</ref> The standard of the facilities at Balmoor was one of the main reasons why Peterhead were elected to the [[Scottish Football League]] in 2000,<ref name = "guide"/> along with [[Elgin City F.C.|Elgin City]].
The record attendance at Balmoor is 4,855, for a [[Scottish Football League Third Division]] match against [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] on 20 January 2013.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rangers.co.uk/match/match-reports/item/3172-peterhead-0-1-rangers|title=Peterhead 0 - 1 Rangers|publisher=Rangers FC|date=20 January 2013|accessdate=20 January 2013|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140107232633/http://www.rangers.co.uk/match/match-reports/item/3172-peterhead-0-1-rangers|archivedate=7 January 2014|df=}}</ref> This broke the previous record crowd of 4,505.
The nearest railway station to Balmoor is [[Aberdeen railway station]], which is {{convert|32|mi}} away.<ref name = "guide"/> This is the greatest distance between a senior league football ground and its nearest railway station in [[Great Britain]].<ref name = "guide"/> Balmoor is located on the [[A982 road]], just north of Peterhead town centre.<ref name = "guide"/>
