'''Cricket NSW''' (formerly known as the ''New South Wales Cricket Association'') is an Australian [[sporting association]] that administers [[cricket in New South Wales]]. It is based at the [[Sydney Cricket Ground]]. The [[Speed Blitz Blues|New South Wales Blues]], the [[Sydney Thunder]] and the [[Sydney Sixers]] are a part of the association.<ref>Cricket NSW (n.d), Cricket NSW, Cricket New South Wales Australia, accessed 4 November 2013, <http://www.cricketnsw.com.au/></ref>
==History==
Cricket NSW was established in 1859.<ref name=history>Cricket NSW (n.d), History, Cricket New South Wales Australia, accessed 4 November 2013,<http://www.cricketnsw.com.au/inside-cricket-nsw/history></ref> [[William Tunks]] and [[Richard Driver]] were the inaugural joint secretaries of the association.<ref name=history></ref> The current CEO is [[Andrew Jones (cricket administrator)|Andrew Jones]].<ref>[http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/sport/cricket/fans-the-number-one-priority-for-new-cricket-nsw-chief-executive-andrew-jones/story-fni2fod7-1226649514881 Fans the number one priority for new Cricket NSW chief executive Andrew Jones] Retrieved 13 May 2015.</ref>
