{{Infobox award | name = The Curt Gowdy Media Award | image = | imagesize = | alt = | caption = | description = | presenter = [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame]] | sponsor = | date = Annual<!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | location = | country = United States | reward = | year = 1990 | website = }}
'''The Curt Gowdy Media Award''' is an annual award given by the [[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame]] to outstanding [[basketball]] [[sportswriters|writers]] and [[Broadcasting of sports events|broadcasters]]. It is named for [[United States|American]] [[sportscaster]] [[Curt Gowdy]], who was the Hall of Fame's [[president]] for seven years.<ref name=HOF>{{cite web |url=http://www.hoophall.com/curt-gowdy-award/ |title=Curt Gowdy Media Award Winners |publisher=[[Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame]] |accessdate=2014-10-19 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208085101/http://www.hoophall.com/curt-gowdy-award/ |archivedate=December 8, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>
