{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}} In [[Australian rules football]], the '''followers''' are the players in the three positions- '''[[Ruckman (Australian rules football position)|ruckman]]''', '''ruck rover''', and '''rover'''. These three players are known as followers because they have traditionally been used as players that follow the ball all around the ground, as opposed to playing in a set position. In recent years, there has been a decreased emphasis on set positions in Australian football. Followers still cover more ground than any other player on the field.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}}
{{Afl-field}}
==Ruckman== The ruckman's job is to contest with the opposing ruckman at centre-bounces that take place at the start of each quarter or after each goal, and at stoppages (i.e., boundary throw ins, ball ups). The ruckman usually uses his height (typically players are over 195&nbsp;cm tall) to palm/tap the ball down so that a ruck rover or rover can run onto it.
Notable ruckmen in Australian football over the years include: * [[Graham Farmer|Graham "Polly" Farmer]] ({{WAFL EP}}, {{AFL Gee}} and {{WAFL WP}}, 1953-1971),<ref name="Pascoe-p38">Pascoe, 1995, p. 38</ref> Sandover Medallist 1956, 1957, 1960; Named first ruck in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[John Nicholls (footballer)|John Nicholls]] ({{AFL Car}}, 1957-1974),<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> Named back pocket in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[Jack Dyer]] * [[Roy Wright (footballer)|Roy Wright]] Brownlow Medallist 1952, 1954 * [[Carl Ditterich]] ({{AFL StK}} and {{AFL Mel}}, 1963-1980)<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> * [[Sam Newman|John "Sam" Newman]] (Geelong, 1964-1980)<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> * [[Gary Dempsey (Australian footballer)|Gary Dempsey]] ({{AFL Foo}} and {{AFL NM}}, 1967-1984),<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> Brownlow Medallist 1975 * [[Don Scott (footballer)|Don Scott]] ({{AFL Haw}}, 1967-1981)<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> * [[Graham Moss]] ({{WAFL Cla}} and {{AFL Ess}}, 1968-1983),<ref name="Pascoe-p39">Pascoe, 1995, p. 39</ref> Brownlow Medallist 1976 * [[Barry Round]] (Footscray and {{AFL Syd}}, 1969-1986),<ref name="Pascoe-p38" /> Brownlow Medallist 1981 * [[Rick Davies (footballer)|Rick Davies]] ({{SANFL Stu}}, Hawthorn and {{SANFL SthA}}, 1970-1986) * [[Simon Madden]] ({{AFL Ess}}, 1974-1992),<ref name="Pascoe-p39" /> Norm Smith Medallist 1985 * [[Peter Moore (Australian rules footballer)|Peter Moore]] ({{AFL Col}} and Melbourne, 1974-1987),<ref name="Pascoe-p39" /> Brownlow Medallist 1979, 1984 * [[Justin Madden]] (Essendon and {{AFL Car}}, 1980-1996)<ref name="Pascoe-p39" /> * [[Paul Salmon]] * [[Jim Stynes]] (Melbourne, 1987-1998),<ref name="Pascoe-p39" /> Brownlow Medallist 1991 * [[Scott Wynd]] ({{AFL WB}}, 1988-2000),<ref name="Pascoe-p39" /> Brownlow Medallist 1992 * [[Peter Everitt]] * [[Dean Cox (Australian footballer)|Dean Cox]] * [[Shaun Rehn]] ({{SANFL WestA}}, {{AFL Ade}} and Hawthorn, 1990-2002) * [[Matthew Primus]] * [[Jeff White (Australian footballer)|Jeff White]] * [[Corey McKernan]] * [[Aaron Sandilands]] * [[Todd Goldstein]] * [[Max Gawn]]
==Ruck rover== Before the 1950s, the role of the ruck-rover was known as the ''follower''. His role was to assist the ruckman and rover at centre bounces by blocking and shepherding them from opposition players.<ref name="Pascoe-p41">Pascoe, 1995, p. 41</ref> This position disappeared in the 1950s with the success of [[Ron Barassi, Jr.]] in a role designated for him by Melbourne coach [[Norm Smith]].<ref name="Pascoe-p41" /> The closest equivalent of the follower position in today's game is known as a [[Australian rules football positions#Taggers|tagger]].<ref name="Pascoe-p41" />
The ruck rover's job is to be directly beneath the flight of the ball when a ruckman taps the ball down, allowing an easy take away, or clearance, from a stoppage. Typically players are not as tall as the ruckman, typically ranging from 170–190&nbsp;cm in height.
Notable followers and ruck-rovers in Australian football over the years include: * [[Ron Barassi, Jr.]] ({{AFL Mel}} and {{AFL Car}}, 1953-1969)<ref name="Pascoe-p41" /> * [[Paul Bagshaw]] ({{SANFL Stu}}, 1964-1980),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sturtfc.com.au/history/team-of-the-century|publisher=sturtfc.com.au|title=Team of the Century|accessdate=14 August 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130730131459/http://sturtfc.com.au/history/team-of-the-century|archivedate=30 July 2013|df=}}</ref> * [[Michael Tuck]] ({{AFL Haw}}, 1972-1991),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hawthornfc.com.au/team%20of%20the%20century/tabid/4819/default.aspx|publisher=hawthornfc.com.au|title=Team of the Century|accessdate=14 August 2012|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110223123516/http://www.hawthornfc.com.au/team%20of%20the%20century/tabid/4819/default.aspx|archivedate=23 February 2011|df=}}</ref> former AFL career games record holder (426) * [[Robert Harvey (footballer)|Robert Harvey]] * [[Chris Judd]] * [[Jobe Watson]] * [[Daniel Kerr]] * [[Garry Hocking]] ({{AFL Gee}}, 1987-2001)<ref name="Pascoe-p42">Pascoe, 1995, p. 42</ref> * [[Michael McGuane]] ({{AFL Col}} and Carlton, 1987-1997)<ref name="Pascoe-p42" /> * [[Brad Sewell]] * [[Trent Cotchin]]
==Rover== The rover is a player who lurks around centre bounces and stoppages to receive the ball from a ruck rover and complete a clearance. Rovers are typically the smallest player on the ground.
Notable rovers in Australian football over the years include: * [[Harry Collier]] ({{AFL Col}}, 1926-1940),<ref name="Pascoe-p40">Pascoe, 1995, p. 40</ref> Brownlow Medallist 1930 * [[Haydn Bunton, Sr.]] ({{AFL Fit}}, {{WAFL Sub}} and {{SANFL Por}}, 1931-1945),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow Medallist 1931, 1932, 1935; Sandover Medallist 1938, 1939, 1941; Named forward pocket in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[Allan Ruthven]] (Fitzroy, 1940-1954)<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow Medallist 1950 * [[Lou Richards]] (Collingwood, 1941-1955)<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> * [[Bill Hutchison]] ({{AFL Ess}}, 1942-1957),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow Medallist 1952, 1953 * [[Steve Marsh (footballer)|Steve Marsh]] ({{WAFL SF}} and {{WAFL EF}}, 1945-1958)<ref name="aflhalloffame">{{cite web|url=http://www.afl.com.au/aflhq/awards/halloffame/players/tabid/856/default.aspx |title=AFL Hall of Fame Players |publisher=[[AFL.com.au]] |accessdate=11 August 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325145459/http://www.afl.com.au/aflhq/awards/halloffame/players/tabid/856/default.aspx |archivedate=25 March 2012 |df= }}</ref> Sandover Medallist 1952 * [[Bob Skilton]] ({{AFL SM}}, 1956-1971),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow Medallist 1959, 1963, 1968; Named rover in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[Bill Goggin]] ({{AFL Gee}}, 1958-1971)<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> * [[Ross G. Smith]] ({{AFL StK}}, 1961-1975),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow medallist 1967 * [[Bill Walker (Australian footballer)|Bill Walker]] ({{WAFL SD}}, 1961-1976),<ref name="aflhalloffame" /> Sandover Medallist 1965, 1966, 1967, 1970 * [[Barry Cable]] ({{WAFL Per}}, {{AFL NM}} and {{WAFL EP}}, 1962-1979),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Sandover Medallist 1964, 1968, 1973 * [[Kevin Bartlett (Australian rules footballer)|Kevin Bartlett]] ({{AFL Ric}}, 1965-1983)<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> * [[Peter Crimmins]] ({{AFL Haw}}, 1966-1971)<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> * [[Leigh Matthews]] (Hawthorn, 1969-1985),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Named forward pocket in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[Tony Liberatore]] ({{AFL WB}}, 1986-2002),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Brownlow Medallist 1990 * [[John Platten]] (Hawthorn, 1986-1997),<ref name="Pascoe-p40" /> Magarey Medallist 1984, Brownlow Medallist 1987 * [[Gary Ablett, Jr.]] (Geelong and {{AFL GC}}, 2002- ),<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.menofleague.com/NewsEvents/2012AustraliaPostAustralianLegendsStamps.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-08-13 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325203931/http://www.menofleague.com/NewsEvents/2012AustraliaPostAustralianLegendsStamps.aspx |archivedate=25 March 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Brownlow Medallist 2009, 2013
