{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Metropolitan Police Sports Club Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[East Molesey]], [[Surrey]] | establishment = 1940 <small>(first recorded match)</small> | seating_capacity = | end1 = Football Ground End | end2 = Tennis Courts End | year1 = 2003 | club1 = [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] | date = 29 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/465.html Ground profile }}
'''Metropolitan Police Sports Club Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[East Molesey]], [[Surrey]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1940, when the Metropolitan Police played a British Empire XI.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/465_misc.html Other matches played on Metropolitan Police Sports Club Ground]</ref>
In 2003, [[Surrey County Cricket Club|Surrey]] used the ground for 2 [[Twenty20]] matches in the [[2003 Twenty20 Cup]], played against [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]] and [[Sussex County Cricket Club|Sussex]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/465_tt.html Twenty20 Matches played on Metropolitan Police Sports Club Ground]</ref>
Being based at a police training college, the ground is used by a number of police teams. A well maintained ground, the [[cricket pavilion]] was constructed in 1983.<ref>[http://www.cricinfo.com/england/content/ground/56969.html Ground profile]</ref>
==Other Metropolitan Police Sports Club Grounds== The Metropolitan Police have other sports clubs at [[Bushey]], [[Chigwell]], and [[Hayes, Bromley|Hayes]].
