}}
'''Munir Abu-Keshek''' is an amateur [[boxing|boxer]] from Palestine.

He won a bronze medal at Light heavyweight at the 2002 Asian Games. In doing so he became the first Palestinian to medal at those games.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amateur-boxing.strefa.pl/Championships/AsianGames2002.html|title=14.Asian Games – Pusan, South Korea – October 1–14 2002|website=amateur-boxing.strefa.pl|accessdate=26 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.haaretz.com/print-edition/sports/palestinian-boxer-wins-landmark-medal-1.31656|title=Palestinian boxer wins landmark medal|author=The Associated Press|work=Haaretz.com}}</ref>

